Rating: 4
Generally I would not rate a recipe if I deviated from the recipe, BUT... I accidentally left out the brandy! I always add a dash of high quality vanilla, regardless if I intend on making sweet or savory crepes. This is the most perfectly simple, delicious, EASY recipe out there. Throw it all together in the blender, pour into a 1/4 cup measuring cup, pour into your crepe pan, swirl around the crepe pan, cook on medium until the edges dry up, flip, let them cook a sec, then separate the crepes between layers of wax paper and it makes enough to enjoy the following week, take to work and snack on! Two great ways to make them: Black Forest ham and Brie with bechamel sauce (and maybe a lil fig jam) if you like the sweet/savoy, or ricotta with a high quality strawberry jam to make a home-made blintz! Regardless of the prep, RAVE reviews are sure to follow! Another note about separating the crepes with wax paper.... ALWAYS do it this way! It you have a stack of left-overs, 20 crepes high, simply fold all four corners of the wax paper in towards the center, press gently to remove the excess air, and place the "packet" of crepes in a large freezer/type ziplock bag -again, don't forget to squeeze out the excess air. Keep them in the fridge for a week, or toss 'em in the freezer. They keep perfect in the fridge for up to a week. My co-workers delighted over week-old crepes w ricotta and strawberry jam!

